    "translations": {
      "en": {
        "summary": "Imam al-Hasan ibn Ali (AS), the second Imam and grandson of Prophet Muhammad (SAWW), addresses the community about three levels of devotion to the Ahl al-Bayt. The highest rank belongs to those who combine sincere love with both physical and verbal support; the middle rank to those who love and speak in their defense; and the baseline reward of Paradise for those who hold love in their hearts even without outward action. This teaching was given in a context where supporters of the Ahl al-Bayt faced persecution, and the Imam distinguished between varying degrees of commitment while affirming that even the minimum of heartfelt love secures salvation.",
        "key_terms": {
          "الغرفة": "Al-ghurfa (the lofty chamber): A high station in Paradise, mentioned in Quran 25:75 as the reward of the patient and devout",
          "نصرنا": "Nasarana (helps us): Active support and defense of the Ahl al-Bayt, both physically and verbally",
          "كف": "Kaffa (withholds/refrains): To hold back or abstain from active involvement"
        },
        "seo_question": "What are the three levels of loving the Ahl al-Bayt according to Imam al-Hasan?"
      },
      "ur": {
        "summary": "امام حسن بن علی علیہما السلام نے اہل بیت سے محبت کے تین درجات بیان فرمائے: دل، ہاتھ اور زبان سے مدد کرنے والا بلند ترین مقام پر ہوگا؛ دل اور زبان سے مدد کرنے والا اس سے ایک درجہ نیچے؛ اور صرف دل سے محبت کرنے والا جنت میں ہوگا۔",
